1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:07,098
Look, most people miss this completely,  Assignors: - RangeAssignor (default): partitions assigned in ranges per topic.

2
00:00:07,048 --> 00:00:08,557
Can be uneven.

3
00:00:08,557 --> 00:00:12,961
RoundRobinAssignor: round-robin across all partitions of all topics.

4
00:00:12,961 --> 00:00:14,230
More even.

5
00:00:14,230 --> 00:00:18,230
StickyAssignor: minimizes partition movement between rebalances.

6
00:00:18,230 --> 00:00:24,192
CooperativeStickyAssignor: incremental rebalance — only revoked partitions pause, others keep consuming.

7
00:00:24,192 --> 00:00:26,567
Eliminates the stop-the-world rebalance.

